# Project Context

This is an iOS application that implements an agent running on a browser triggered after the user uses a hold-to-record audio feature with a modern SwiftUI interface. The app allows users to record audio by holding a microphone button, and automatically uploads the recording to a backend server.

The project utilizes a Python package called browser_use to automate the tasks in the backend.

## Key Features
- Hold-to-record functionality
- Real-time audio recording
- Automatic upload to backend server
- Modern SwiftUI interface with animations

## Technical Stack
- SwiftUI for UI
- FastAPI backend
